B. Jacobians for UKF

In [16], the authors present a new interpretation of the UKF as a Linear Regression Kalman Filter (LRKF). In LRKF, we seek to ï¬nd the optimal linear approximation y = Ax + b + e of the nonlinear function (4) given a weighted discrete (or sigma points (6)) representation of the distribution N (xË†, Pxx). The objective is to ï¬nd the regression matrix A and vector b that minimize the linearizion error e:

2n
