erogeneous sensors that yield either absolute or relative observations at different and varying time intervals. Our approach generates high rate state estimates in real-time for autonomous ï¬‚ight. The proposed approach runs onboard our new 1.9 kg MAV platform equipped with multiple heterogeneous sensors. We demonstrate the robustness of our framework in large-scale, indoor and outdoor autonomous ï¬‚ight experiments that involves traversal through a industrial complex and a tree-lined campus.
In the near future, we would like to integrate higher level planning and situational awareness on our MAV platform to achieve fully autonomous operation across large-scale complex environments.
